I want to create a Golang service that is kind of like traefik: An HTTPS proxy server
with The ability to set up and manage multiple virtual dev environments.  It would also
have a web-based management interface.   Here are some of the features:

It would use a self-signed cert, likely a wildcard like "*.sean.realgo.com".  It would
have an API and a CLI tool that would allow functions like:

    - add/delete load balancer: Add/delete a name to the load balancer like
      "RG-27788-cpcart-cleanups.sean.realgo.com"
    - request/return a port: The service would have a range of ports that it would keep track of
      and give back (and track) a port.  For example, maybe we have defined that ports
      9000-9999 are available, and it has tracked that it has previously given out
      9000-9010, so it now give out 9011.
    - add/delete a mapping to a load balancer: Given a load balancer, map port X on it to
      go to port Y on the local machine.  For example, "Forward connections on
      RG-27788-cpcart-cleanups.sean.realgo.com on port 443 to port 9011 on localhost".

Forwardings could be localhost or could be another hostname, and the endpoint could be
HTTPS or just regular HTTP.  Make a decision about whether a general TCP/TLS+TCP endpoint
should be supported as well, this could be a future decision.  We probably also need to
be able to support connections that have a self-signed CA cert, and maybe also support a
"don't verify remote cert" option, as this is a development server.

There would be a web management UI available on the proxy so that you could see the
configured load balancers, easily hit the website on that load balancer, and see what
ports are mapped for it.

